latestPosts.caption:
Celebrating the legacy of Burberry’s iconic trench coat—that was crafted over 100 years ago—The Word. presented a special series with some of the country’s leading cultural voices donning the iconic garment.

This special series was photographed against the travelling Burberry Archive Trench Exhibition, which was on display at DLF Emporio in the capital. Here, historic pieces were recreated from World War II, 1927, and 1937.

Palak Shah, AD Singh, Prateek Jain and Gautam Seth, Viraj Khanna, and Tarini Seth are wearing Trench Coats by @burberry

Editor-in-Chief: Nandini Bhalla (@nandinibhalla)
Photographer: Anubhav Sood (@anubhav_sood)
Styling & Creative Direction: Gopalika Virmani (@gopalikavirmani)
Hair & Make-up: Geet Sukhani (@geetsukhani ) 
Styling Assts: @rizarizvi_official , @saumyasahni_ , @hansikabawejaa
Production: @mmcworld_official @i.m.vishalbansal
